def: Of his or its own kind.
Enlargement or extension of business transaction; esp.,increase of the circulation of bank notes.
The act of addressing or directing one's course. [Rare & Obs.]Chapman.
Of or pertaining to the cremaster; as, the cremasteric artery.
A poem of eight lines. [Obs.] Selden
Having a fringe of feathers, as the legs of certian birds; orof hairs, as the legs of a setter dog.
The state or quality of being luxuriant; luxuriance.Flowers grow up in the garden in the greatest luxuriancy andprofusion. Spectator.
Lying or remaining in a place; hence, resident; as, legerambassador.
The state of being uncivilized; want of civilization;barbarism.
A squabble; a tumult; a noisy disturbance; as, to raise abobbery. [Low] Halliwell.

A solid bounded by twenty sides or faces. Regular icosahedron,one of the five regular polyhedrons, bounded by twenty equilateraltriangules. Five triangules meet to form each solid angle of thepolyhedron.
